README openvpn

KERNEL CONFIGURATION

	Enable "Universal TUN/TAP device driver support" in your kernel:

	Device Drivers  --->
	  [*] Network device support  --->
	    [*] Network core driver support
	    <*>   Universal TUN/TAP device driver support
	          CONFIG_TUN=y|m

KERNEL MODULE

	If you compiled device driver as a loadable kernel module, add the
	following lines to /etc/rc.modules to autoload module needed by
	openvpn:

		# Universal TUN/TAP device driver
		/sbin/modprobe tun

End of file.
